      <center><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#792022"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#A0332E"><tr><td>
<font class="pn-title">BFA - Policy and Procedure</font><br /><br /><font class="pn-normal">(506 total words in this text)</font><br /><font class="pn-normal">(42 Reads)</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=printpage&amp;artid=2"><img src="modules/Sections/images/print.gif" border="0" Alt="Printer friendly page"></a></font><br /><br /><font class="pn-normal"><b>PURPOSE AND PRECEDENCE</b> - The purpose of this alliance is to establish stronger bonds with other existing guilds so that we may use this alliance to benefit each other in ways we could not do alone. Once a guild has established an alliance with the BFA, it must be communicated to all of the guild members to inform them of the arrangement. Members of each of the guilds are expected to be aware of the alliance and adhere to the policies and regulations at all times both in character and out of character. <br><br>

<b>JOINING</b> - The BFA will offer alliances to other guilds and other guilds may approach the BFA to join the alliance. Each potential allying guild will be thoroughly researched by The Council. Also, members of BFA will group with them when possible. There will then be a vote held among the BFA on allowing in the potential guild. If the majority of the vote is in favor, then the guild will be made an official ally of BFA. If an allied guild or potential ally have alliances already in place, those guilds are not considered part of the BFA, but must separately submit for alliance. For more information on becoming part of the BFA, please visit the Joining Us section of our site. <br><br>

<b>THE COUNCIL</b> - The Council will be made up of one elected member of each guild. It will be up to these elected individuals to be the voice for their guild in any proceedings, arbitrations and disputes. Council members, though they have added burdens, will receive no special benefits. <br><br>

<b>COMMITMENT</b> - When a guild becomes part of BFA, their members not only wear their guild flag, but also represent the BFA. We hope they do so with honor. Members of the BFA are encouraged to group together outside of official raids. This is not mandatory, but makes for better guild relations and better awareness of individual strengths and weaknesses as a resource to each other as well as promoting bonding. <br><br>

In Norrath, certain things are considered disrespect. Among these offences are, insult or harassment (beyond the tolerable amounts that can occur from time to time), theft or betrayal, multiple training, multiple KSing, and slander. Providing the severity of the case and proof given, any intentional or repeated shows of disrespect towards an allied guild or any other persons will be dealt with through the following steps: <br><br>

<ul><li>- First Offense: Verbal Warning to the individual(s). <br>
<li>- Second Offense: Written warning and investigation into the problem by The Council. <br>
<li>- Third Offense: Further investigation with possible reprimand of suspension and/or removal of person or guild from the alliance. </ul><br><br>

<b>PROMOTING THE FLAME</b> - Above all things within this alliance, is the promotion of friendship, laughter, adventure, merriment and entertainment. In other words, have a good time, make some friends, stop and smell the flowers and enjoy the view. Together we will be able to see and do many things, but all of that is fruitless if we did not have fun doing it!</font></td></tr><tr><td align="center"> &nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br />[ <a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=listarticles&amp;secid=1">Back to Burning Flame Alliance</a> | <a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;listsections">Sections index</a> ]</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</center></td>
      <td align="center" background="themes/ArvidNocturne/images/bg2.gif"> 
      </td>
